I understand mistakes happen during a pandemic. This is a fault of the sweetgreen application and the sweetgreen customer service team more than the location.  After choosing a pickup time on the application, my food wasn't ready for an 45 minutes. I waited for this food in a crowd of other angry guests who were also waiting for their food, during this pandemic. When I finally received my food, because of how swamped the location was, it was understandably completely wrong and largely inedible.  I reached out to the customer experience team roughly five times over the course of 2 weeks, simply for a refund for an awful experience with inedible food. I received first a "spend $25 to save $5" coupon, which after further emails explaining my issue, they added on a $15 coupon. $15 was not even a third of what my meal cost.  I understand mistakes happen, especially during a pandemic. Every other restaurant I've been to during this pandemic has made the issue right as best they could.  If you care at all about customer experience, and you care at all that a restaurant appreciates your business, do not go to sweetgreen.

The girl behind the counter was helping another woman and I was waiting to pay and then she turned to me and said ok I can help you. I said to her I got the one salad (the woman in front of me who hadn't paid yet got 3 salads) so I just wanted to remind her just incase she got confused and she said "yea I know". Then a second after she swipes my card she says "oh no" then tells me how she made a mistake charged me $40 for the woman's order in front of me. So ok human error even though I reminded her....it's ok. Then a manager comes over and I'm standing there for 5 min and I was like Can I please have a refund? And then the guy said they can't do refunds there and I had to write down all of my info so they could have it done by headquarters or something. I was in a rush so I was a little annoyed but I said fine and wrote it down. He said he would get back to me that day with an email and I would refunded within 24 hrs.......48 hrs passes and I try calling and I can't get in touch... So I went there and they told me it was going to take a little longer and they have me on a list. And I called my bank and tried to make a claim to get my money back and that didn't work. So now it is a month later and I paid $40 for a $10 salad. :/
